// RUN: %arche test %s

// Regression: a doc comment that follows a complete declaration is absorbed by
// the parser as a trailing leaf of the PREVIOUS decl's node, not a root-level
// sibling. The doc query must still attach it to the following decl, so the
// second function's example must be found and run.

/// The first function (documented, no example).
first :: func (a: int) -> int {
  return a;
}

/// The second function.
///
/// # Example
/// ```arche
/// assert(second(3) == 9, "second broken\n");
/// ```
second :: func (a: int) -> int {
  return a * a;
}
